answerText: Feynman Diagrams [or Stueckelberg diagrams; or Feynman-Dyson diagrams; or Dyson graphs][10] In a Feynman diagram, a particle line going backward in time represents this type of particle in relation to the depicted one. The positron is this type of particle for the electron.
